The paper deals with the problem of partitioning a text to improve its compression, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions dynamic programming (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DC) as approaches to solving the problem. Finally, the paper provides a new algorithm that guarantees a certain level of compression performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
